<C>__{perry}
<P>__{(looks at truman; evenly)}
<D>__{i was ten, i wet the bed, the nuns at the orphanage hated the smell. first month one of them found me shivering just trying to get through the night. the sister pulled back the covers and shined her flashlight to see what i'd did. the sheets were wet. she hit me so many times with that flashlight she broke it.}
<P>__{(he shrugs)}
<D>__{that night i dreamed about the yellow bird. tall. yellow like the sun. it picked me up and it clawed the nun's eyes and it lifted me into the sky.}
